<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "GovernmentService",
      "name": "{{ country }} Visa Application Service",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "GovernmentOrganization",
        "name": "{{ authority.name }}"
      },
      "areaServed": "India"
    }
  ]
}
</script>

# <img src="https://flagcdn.com/48x36/{{ iso_code | default('xx') | lower }}.png" alt="{{ country }} flag" class="atlas-flag"> {{ country }} Visa Requirements for Indian Citizens

<div class="atlas-country-cards" markdown>
<div class="atlas-card atlas-card--overview" markdown>

### Visa Info

* **Visa Type:** {{ visa_type | default("Standard Visa") }}
* **Entry Type:** {{ entry_type | default("Single Entry") }}
* **Maximum Stay:** {{ max_stay | default("Varies") }}
* **Visa Validity:** {{ visa_validity | default("Refer to visa stamp") }}
* **Visa Fee:** ₹{{ requirements.visa_fee_inr }}
* **Processing Time:** {{ requirements.processing_days }} working days
* **Photo Spec:** {{ requirements.photo_specs.dimensions }}, {{ requirements.photo_specs.bg_color }} bg

</div>
<div class="atlas-card atlas-card--authority" markdown>

### Authority & Access

* **Issuing Authority:** {{ authority.name }}
* **Processor:** {{ authority.processor }}
* **Official Portal:** [Visit portal]({{ authority.official_portal }})

</div>
</div>

## Document Checklist

{%- if visa_types and visa_types | length > 1 %}
<div class="atlas-vtype-selector" role="tablist" aria-label="Select visa type" data-country="{{ country | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}">
  {%- for vtype, vdata in visa_types.items() %}
  <button class="atlas-vtype-tab{% if loop.first %} atlas-vtype-tab--active{% endif %}" role="tab" data-vtype="{{ vtype }}">{{ vdata.label }}</button>
  {%- endfor %}
</div>
{%- endif %}

<div class="atlas-occ-selector" role="group" aria-label="Select applicant type">
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn atlas-occ-btn--active" data-occ="salaried">Salaried</button>
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn" data-occ="self_employed">Self-employed</button>
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn" data-occ="business_owner">Business owner</button>
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn" data-occ="student">Student</button>
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn" data-occ="homemaker">Homemaker</button>
  <button class="atlas-occ-btn" data-occ="retired">Retired</button>
</div>

<div class="atlas-checklist" data-country="{{ country | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}">
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="passport">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Valid passport — minimum {{ passport_validity_months | default(6) }} months validity beyond your trip end date, with {{ blank_pages_required | default(2) }}+ blank pages</span>
  </label>
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="photos">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Passport-size photographs — {{ requirements.photo_specs.dimensions }}, {{ requirements.photo_specs.bg_color }} background</span>
  </label>
{%- if visa_types %}
  {%- for vtype, vdata in visa_types.items() %}
    {%- set is_first_type = loop.first %}
    {%- for doc in vdata.documents %}
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item atlas-checklist__item--vtype" data-vtype="{{ vtype }}"{% if not is_first_type %} hidden{% endif %}>
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="vt-{{ vtype }}-{{ loop.index }}">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">{{ doc }}</span>
  </label>
    {%- endfor %}
  {%- endfor %}
{%- else %}
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="application-form">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Completed visa application form</span>
  </label>
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="flight-tickets">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Confirmed return flight tickets</span>
  </label>
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="accommodation">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Proof of accommodation — hotel booking or invitation letter</span>
  </label>
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="travel-insurance">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Travel insurance policy — covering the full duration of stay</span>
  </label>
{%- endif %}
{%- for doc in requirements.financial_documents %}
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item atlas-checklist__item--occ" data-occ="salaried">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="fin-salaried-{{ loop.index }}">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">{{ doc }}</span>
  </label>
{%- endfor %}
{%- if requirements.occupation_documents %}
  {%- for occ_type, docs in requirements.occupation_documents.items() %}
    {%- for doc in docs %}
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item atlas-checklist__item--occ" data-occ="{{ occ_type }}" hidden>
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="fin-{{ occ_type }}-{{ loop.index }}">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">{{ doc }}</span>
  </label>
    {%- endfor %}
  {%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
  <label class="atlas-checklist__item">
    <input type="checkbox" data-key="fee-receipt">
    <span class="atlas-checklist__text">Visa fee payment — ₹{{ requirements.visa_fee_inr }}</span>
  </label>
</div>

<details class="atlas-cover-letter">
<summary>Sample cover letter for {{ country }} {{ visa_type }}</summary>
<div class="atlas-cover-letter__body">
<pre class="atlas-cover-letter__text">
To,
The Visa Officer
{{ authority.name }}

Subject: Application for {{ visa_type }} — {{ country }}

Dear Visa Officer,

I, [YOUR FULL NAME], a citizen of India (Passport No. [XXXXXXXX], valid
until [DD/MM/YYYY]), respectfully submit my application for a {{ visa_type }}
to {{ country }}.

PURPOSE OF VISIT
The purpose of my visit is [tourism / business / attending a conference /
visiting family or friends]. I plan to travel from [DEPARTURE DATE] to
[RETURN DATE], a total stay of approximately [XX] days.

ACCOMMODATION
I will be staying at [Hotel name and address / Name and address of host].

FINANCIAL CAPABILITY
I have adequate financial resources to support my stay in {{ country }} and
my return to India. Supporting bank statements and financial documents are
enclosed.

I solemnly affirm that I will comply with all visa conditions and depart
from {{ country }} on or before the expiry of my visa. I have strong ties
to India — [employment / business / property / family] — that ensure my
timely return.

All required supporting documents are enclosed as per the requirements of
{{ authority.name }}.

Yours faithfully,

[YOUR FULL NAME]
[Date]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
</pre>
<button class="atlas-cover-letter__copy" type="button">Copy to clipboard</button>
</div>
</details>

{%- if jurisdiction %}

## Where to Apply

<div class="atlas-jurisdiction" markdown>

Your application must be submitted to the consular office responsible for your **Indian state of residence**.

{%- for office in jurisdiction %}

<div class="atlas-jurisdiction__office" markdown>

**{{ office.office }}**

{{ office.covers | join(" · ") }}

</div>
{%- endfor %}

</div>
{%- endif %}

{%- if transit %}

## Transit Rules

<div class="atlas-transit" markdown>

**Transit visa required:** {{ "Yes" if transit.visa_required else "No" }}

{%- if transit.exceptions %}

**Exceptions:**

{%- for exc in transit.exceptions %}
- {{ exc }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}

{%- if transit.notes %}

**Note:** {{ transit.notes }}
{%- endif %}

</div>
{%- endif %}

{%- if exemptions %}

## Visa Exemptions & Indian Privilege

<div class="atlas-exemptions" markdown>

Indian passport holders may qualify for simplified or waived visa requirements if they hold certain third-party visas or travel documents.

{%- for ex in exemptions %}

<div class="atlas-exemption-card" markdown>

| | |
|---|---|
| **If you hold** | {{ ex.holding }} |
| **You get** | {{ ex.grants }} |
| **Conditions** | {{ ex.conditions }} |
{%- if ex.source %}
| **Source** | [Verify ↗]({{ ex.source }}) |
{%- endif %}

</div>
{%- endfor %}

</div>
{%- endif %}

{%- if ecr %}

## ECR / Non-ECR Passport

<div class="atlas-ecr atlas-ecr--{{ 'active' if ecr.applies else 'inactive' }}" markdown>

**ECR rules apply:** {{ "Yes — read carefully" if ecr.applies else "No" }}

{{ ecr.note }}

</div>
{%- endif %}

## Public Health & Vaccinations

<div class="atlas-health" markdown>

{% if health and health.vaccinations -%}
**Recommended Vaccinations:** {{ health.vaccinations }}
{%- else -%}
**Recommended Vaccinations:** Routine vaccinations (MMR, DPT, Polio). Hepatitis A and Typhoid recommended for most travellers.
{%- endif %}

{% if health and health.insurance -%}
**Health Insurance:** {{ health.insurance }}
{%- else -%}
**Health Insurance:** Comprehensive travel health insurance strongly recommended.
{%- endif %}

{% if health and health.notes -%}
**Advisory:** {{ health.notes }}
{%- else -%}
**Advisory:** Check the latest entry requirements on the official embassy portal before travel.
{%- endif %}

</div>

{%- if biometrics %}

## Biometrics

<div class="atlas-biometrics" markdown>

**Biometrics required:** {{ "Yes" if biometrics.required else "No" }}
{%- if biometrics.validity_months %}

**Validity:** {{ biometrics.validity_months }} months — if previously captured within this period at any participating center, you may not need to appear in person.
{%- endif %}

{{ biometrics.note }}

</div>
{%- endif %}

{%- if changelog %}

## Change Log

<div class="atlas-changelog" markdown>

| Date | Type | Change | Source |
|------|------|--------|--------|
{%- for entry in changelog %}
| {{ entry.date }} | <span class="atlas-changelog__tag atlas-changelog__tag--{{ entry.type | lower }}">{{ entry.type }}</span> | {{ entry.description }} | [↗]({{ entry.source }}) |
{%- endfor %}

</div>
{%- endif %}

---
*Data is verified against official consular sources.*
